<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910308-0010</DOCNO><DOCID>910308-0010.</DOCID><HL>   Samsung to Establish Subsidiary</HL><DATE>03/08/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A7B</SO><CO>   C.SSG</CO><IN>INSURANCE (INS)LIFE INSURANCE (INL)</IN><LP>   SEOUL -- Samsung Life Insurance Co., South Korea's largestinsurance firm, will set up a subsidiary in the Britishchannel islands banking center of Jersey to invest infinancial assets, company officials said.   The financial arm of the Samsung Business Group will setup the subsidiary, capitalized at $10 million, to invest inEuropean securities and to prepare for the integration of theEuropean markets, they added.</LP><TEXT>   Samsung's subsidiary will be South Korea's first overseasoutlet solely dedicated to investment in financial assets.Samsung Life Insurance is the country's largest institutionalinvestor. Its total investments in stocks and bonds is 3trillion won ($4.18 billion). Its assets stand at 10 trillionwon.</TEXT></DOC>